    "long_instructions": "# Do This:\r\n1. **Discuss:** What code would you need to add to the `turn_around()` function definition that would make the Painter turn around to face the opposite direction? <br>\r\n2. **Modify:** Implement your ideas, run and test your code. <br>\r\n3. **Comment:** Use the `#` to add a comment above the `turn_around()` function to explain what it does. <br>\r\n4. **Modify:** Use your new function with other functions and Painter methods to paint the end of each street.\r\n\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background-color: #E0D1EC; border: 1px solid #9660bf; border-radius: 5px; font-size: 1.1em; padding: 15px; margin-bottom: 10px; color: black;\">\r\n<h5><strong>📝 Backpack</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://images.code.org/62f09f868980e7c875370cc83b633d04-Screenshot 2025-01-31 144022.png\" style=\"width: 75px; float: right;\">\r\n\r\nSave your `turn_around()` function to the Backpack! You will be able to copy and paste any code segments saved there in future levels and lessons!\r\n\r\n</div>",
    "start_sources": {
      "files": {
        "0": {
          "id": "0",
          "name": "main.py",
          "language": "py",
          "contents": "from neighborhood import Painter\n\nbob = Painter()\nbob.take_paint()\n\ndef turn_around():\n  # Add code here for the turn_around() function\n\n\n# Add code below to paint the end of each street\nturn_around()\n",
          "folderId": "0",
          "active": true,
          "open": true
        }
      },
      "folders": {
      }
